<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1436,1744,2010]" box="[151,255,1744,1770]" pageId="34" pageNumber="129">Remarks</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1436,1744,2010]" lastBlockId="35.[151,1437,152,378]" lastPageId="35" lastPageNumber="130" pageId="34" pageNumber="129">
In 
<number box="[230,289,1784,1810]" pageId="34" pageNumber="129" value="1929.0">1929</number>
Burton erected a genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Burton, 1929" authorityName="Burton" authorityYear="1929" box="[575,686,1784,1809]" class="Demospongiae" family="Suberitidae" genus="Suberella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Suberitida" pageId="34" pageNumber="129" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[575,686,1784,1809]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="129">Suberella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for a new species, 
<taxonomicName box="[912,1035,1784,1809]" class="Demospongiae" family="Suberitidae" genus="Suberites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="34" pageNumber="129" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="topsenti">
<emphasis box="[912,1035,1784,1809]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="129">S. topsenti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
described by him from McMurdo Sound, 
<taxonomicName box="[245,371,1824,1850]" class="Demospongiae" family="Polymastiidae" genus="Radiella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="34" pageNumber="133" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="antarctica">
<collectingCountry box="[245,371,1824,1850]" name="Antarctica" pageId="34" pageNumber="129">Antarctica</collectingCountry>
</taxonomicName>
. He also allocated the 
<collectingCountry box="[655,764,1824,1850]" name="Antarctica" pageId="34" pageNumber="129">Antarctic</collectingCountry>
specimens, previously identified by 
<bibRefCitation author="Topsent" box="[1216,1398,1824,1850]" pageId="34" pageNumber="135" refString="Topsent, E. (1915) Spongiaires recueillis par la &quot; Scotia &quot; dans l'Antarctique (1903 - 1904). Supplement. Transactions of the Royal Society of Edinburgh, 51 (1 - 2), 35 - 43." type="journal article" year="1915">
Topsent (
<number box="[1328,1389,1824,1850]" pageId="34" pageNumber="129" value="1915.0">1915</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName authority="Carter, 1880" authorityName="Carter" authorityYear="1880" box="[151,554,1864,1890]" class="Demospongiae" family="Suberitidae" genus="Suberites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="34" pageNumber="129" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="montiniger">
<emphasis box="[151,396,1864,1889]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="129">Suberites montiniger</emphasis>
Carter, 
<number box="[493,554,1864,1890]" pageId="34" pageNumber="129" value="1880.0">1880</number>
</taxonomicName>
, to 
<taxonomicName authority="Burton, 1929" authorityName="Burton" authorityYear="1929" box="[599,810,1864,1889]" class="Demospongiae" family="Suberitidae" genus="Suberella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Suberitida" pageId="34" pageNumber="129" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="topsenti">
<emphasis box="[599,810,1864,1889]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="129">Suberella topsenti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In fact, 
<taxonomicName box="[919,1078,1864,1889]" class="Demospongiae" family="Suberitidae" genus="Suberites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="34" pageNumber="129" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="montiniger">
<emphasis box="[919,1078,1864,1889]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="129">S. montiniger</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
had been originally described from the Arctic (Carter 
<number box="[429,492,1904,1930]" pageId="34" pageNumber="129" value="1880.0">1880</number>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Burton" box="[512,679,1904,1930]" pageId="34" pageNumber="133" refString="Burton, M. (1929) Porifera. Part II. Antarctic sponges. British Antarctic (&quot; Terra Nova &quot;) Expedition, 1910. Natural History Report, Zoology, 6 (4), 393 - 458." type="journal article" year="1929">
Burton (
<number box="[610,671,1904,1930]" pageId="34" pageNumber="129" value="1929.0">1929</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName authority="Burton, 1929" authorityName="Burton" authorityYear="1929" box="[822,933,1904,1929]" class="Demospongiae" family="Suberitidae" genus="Suberella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Suberitida" pageId="34" pageNumber="129" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[822,933,1904,1929]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="129">Suberella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to be an evolutionary step between 
<taxonomicName class="Demospongiae" family="Suberitidae" genus="Suberites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="34" pageNumber="129" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="129">Suberites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[249,441,1944,1969]" class="Demospongiae" family="Suberitidae" genus="Pseudosuberites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="34" pageNumber="129" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[249,441,1944,1969]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="129">Pseudosuberites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Belatedly, 
<bibRefCitation author="Burton" box="[581,748,1944,1970]" pageId="34" pageNumber="133" refString="Burton, M. (1930) Additions to the Sponge Fauna of the Gulf of Manaar. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, (10) 5 (30), 665 - 676." type="journal article" year="1930">
Burton (
<number box="[679,740,1944,1970]" pageId="34" pageNumber="129" value="1930.0">1930</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
discovered that 
<taxonomicName authority="Burton, 1929" authorityName="Burton" authorityYear="1929" box="[942,1053,1944,1969]" class="Demospongiae" family="Suberitidae" genus="Suberella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Suberitida" pageId="34" pageNumber="129" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[942,1053,1944,1969]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="129">Suberella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
had been preoccupied by 
<bibRefCitation author="Thiele" pageId="34" pageNumber="135" refString="Thiele, J. (1905) Die Kiesel- und Hornschwamme der Sammlung Plate. Zoologische Jahrbucher, Supplement 6 (Fauna Chiliensis III), 407 - 496." type="book chapter" year="1905">
Thiele (
<number box="[160,223,1984,2010]" pageId="34" pageNumber="129" value="1905.0">1905</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, and erected 
<taxonomicName authority="Burton, 1930" authorityName="Burton" authorityYear="1930" box="[384,551,1984,2009]" class="Demospongiae" family="Suberitidae" genus="Laxosuberella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Suberitida" pageId="34" pageNumber="129" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[384,551,1984,2009]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="129">Laxosuberella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with 
<typeStatus box="[617,668,1984,2010]" pageId="34" pageNumber="129">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Burton, 1929" authorityName="Burton" authorityYear="1929" box="[766,890,1984,2009]" class="Demospongiae" family="Suberitidae" genus="Suberella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Suberitida" pageId="34" pageNumber="129" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="topsenti">
<emphasis box="[766,890,1984,2009]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="129">L. topsenti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a replacement of 
<taxonomicName authority="Burton, 1929" authorityName="Burton" authorityYear="1929" box="[1129,1340,1984,2009]" class="Demospongiae" family="Suberitidae" genus="Suberella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Suberitida" pageId="34" pageNumber="129" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="topsenti">
<emphasis box="[1129,1340,1984,2009]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="129">Suberella topsenti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Koltun" lastPageId="35" lastPageNumber="130" pageId="34" pageNumber="134" refString="Koltun, V. M. (1964) Sponges of the Antarctic. Part 1. Tetraxonida and Cornacuspongida. In: Pavlovskii, E. P., Andriyashev, A. P. &amp; Ushakov, P. V. (Eds.), Biological Reports of the Soviet Antarctic Expedition (1955 - 1958), Explorations of the fauna of the seas. Vol. 2 (10). Academy of Sciences of the USSR, Nauka, Moscow-Leningrad, 6 - 133, 443 - 448." type="journal article" year="1964">
Koltun (
<number box="[159,222,152,178]" pageId="35" pageNumber="130" value="1964.0">1964</number>
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Koltun" box="[234,294,152,178]" pageId="35" pageNumber="134" refString="Koltun, V. M. (1976) Porifera. Part I: Antarctic sponges. B. A. N. Z. Antarctic Research Expedition 1929 - 1931 Reports, Ser. B (Zoology and Botany), 9 (4), 147 - 198." type="journal article" year="1976">
<number box="[234,294,152,178]" pageId="35" pageNumber="130" value="1976.0">1976</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) disagreed with Burton and reverted 
<taxonomicName box="[728,886,152,177]" class="Demospongiae" family="Suberitidae" genus="Suberites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="35" pageNumber="130" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="montiniger">
<emphasis box="[728,886,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="130">S. montiniger</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
again. Herein we follow van 
<bibRefCitation author="Soest" box="[1230,1379,152,178]" pageId="35" pageNumber="135" refString="Soest, R. W. M. van (2002) Family Suberitidae Schmidt, 1870. In: Hooper, J. N. A. &amp; van Soest, R. W. M. (Eds.), Systema Porifera. A Guide to the Classification of Sponges. Vol. 1. Kluwer Academic / Plenum Publishers, New York, pp. 227 - 244." type="book chapter" year="2002">
Soest (
<number box="[1309,1371,152,178]" pageId="35" pageNumber="130" value="2002.0">2002</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
who recently advocated the validity of 
<taxonomicName authority="Burton, 1929" authorityName="Burton" authorityYear="1929" box="[551,644,192,217]" class="Demospongiae" family="Suberitidae" genus="Suberella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Suberitida" pageId="35" pageNumber="130" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="topsenti">
<emphasis box="[551,644,192,217]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="130">topsenti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a species, but placed it in 
<taxonomicName box="[985,1094,192,217]" class="Demospongiae" family="Suberitidae" genus="Suberites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hadromerida" pageId="35" pageNumber="130" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[985,1094,192,217]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="130">Suberites</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The taxonomic history of 
<taxonomicName authority="Burton, 1929" authorityName="Burton" authorityYear="1929" class="Demospongiae" family="Suberitidae" genus="Suberella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Suberitida" pageId="35" pageNumber="130" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="topsenti">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="130">S. topsenti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is described in detail by the latter author. We should only emphasize the lobate tyles of the subtylostyles in our sponges which have not been previously mentioned by any author, and the larger size of the choanosomal spicules in comparison with those observed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Koltun" box="[836,1003,312,338]" pageId="35" pageNumber="134" refString="Koltun, V. M. (1964) Sponges of the Antarctic. Part 1. Tetraxonida and Cornacuspongida. In: Pavlovskii, E. P., Andriyashev, A. P. &amp; Ushakov, P. V. (Eds.), Biological Reports of the Soviet Antarctic Expedition (1955 - 1958), Explorations of the fauna of the seas. Vol. 2 (10). Academy of Sciences of the USSR, Nauka, Moscow-Leningrad, 6 - 133, 443 - 448." type="journal article" year="1964">
Koltun (
<number box="[934,995,312,338]" pageId="35" pageNumber="130" value="1964.0">1964</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
who did not distinguish two spicule categories either.
</paragraph>
